\f0\b\fs52 \cf2 Zucchini Gratin\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Yield: 
\b0 6 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}6 tablespoons (3/4 stick) unsalted butter, plus extra for topping\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound yellow onions, cut in 1/2 and sliced (3 large)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 pounds zucchini, sliced 1/4-inch thick (4 zucchini)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 kosher salt}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup hot {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/milk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 milk}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup fresh bread crumbs\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup grated Gruyere\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/melt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Melt}} the butter in a very large (12-inch) saute pan and cook the onions over low heat for 20 minutes, or until tender but not browned. Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/zucchini/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 zucchini}} and cook, covered, for 10 minutes, or until tender. Add the salt, pepper, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/nutmeg/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 nutmeg}} and cook uncovered for 5 more minutes. Stir in the flour. Add the hot milk and cook over low heat for a few minutes, until it makes a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 sauce}}. Pour the mixture into an 8 by 10-inch {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookware-and-bakeware-materials/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 baking dish}}.\
Combine the bread crumbs and Gruyere and sprinkle on top of the zucchini mixture. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dot/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Dot}} with 1 tablespoon of butter cut into small bits and bake for 20 minutes, or until bubbly and browned.\
